    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Asymmetric Cryptography</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: monospace;\n            background-color: white;\n        }\n        input, button {\n            padding: 5px;\n            margin: 5px;\n            border: 1px solid black;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n        }\n        button {\n            background-color: black;\n            color: white;\n            border: none;\n            padding: 10px 20px;\n            cursor: pointer;\n        }\n        button:hover {\n            background-color: darkred;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <h1>Asymmetric Cryptography</h1>\n    <p>This is a simple implementation of asymmetric cryptography.</p>\n    <h2>How it works</h2>\n    <p>Asymmetric cryptography is a method of encrypting data using a pair of keys: a public key for encryption and a private key for decryption.</p>\n    <p>Here's a simple example of how it works:</p>\n    <p>Public Key: 1234567890\n    Private Key: 9876543210</p>\n    <h2>Generating Keys</h2>\n    <form>\n        <label for=\"public-key\">Public Key:</label>\n        <input type=\"text\" id=\"public-key\" name=\"public-key\" value=\"1234567890\" readonly>\n        <button type=\"button\">Generate Key</button>\n    </form>\n    <form>\n        <label for=\"private-key\">Private Key:</label>\n        <input type=\"text\" id=\"private-key\" name=\"private-key\" value=\"9876543210\" readonly>\n        <button type=\"button\">Generate Key</button>\n    </form>\n    <h2>Encrypting Data</h2>\n    <form>\n        <label for=\"data\">Data:</label>\n        <textarea id=\"data\" name=\"data\" readonly></textarea>\n        <button type=\"button\">Encrypt</button>\n    </form>\n    <h2>Decrypting Data</h2>\n    <form>\n        <label for=\"encrypted-data\">Encrypted Data:</label>\n        <textarea id=\"encrypted-data\" name=\"encrypted-data\" readonly></textarea>\n        <button type=\"button\">Decrypt</button>\n    </form>\n    <script>\n        const publicKey = document.getElementById('public-key').value;\n        const privateKey = document.getElementById('private-key').value;\n        const data = document.getElementById('data').value;\n\n        const encryptButton = document.getElementById('encrypt');\n        const decryptButton = document.getElementById('decrypt');\n\n        encryptButton.addEventListener('click', () => {\n            const encryptedData = encrypt(publicKey, data);\n            document.getElementById('encrypted-data').value = encryptedData;\n        });\n\n        decryptButton.addEventListener('click', () => {\n            const decryptedData = decrypt(privateKey, data);\n            document.getElementById('data').value = decryptedData;\n        });\n\n        function encrypt(key, data) {\n            // Simple encryption algorithm\n            const encryptedData = crypto.subtle.encrypt({\n                name: 'AES-GCM',\n                iv: crypto.randomBytes(12),\n            }, publicKey, Buffer.from(data, 'utf8'));\n            return encryptedData;\n        }\n\n        function decrypt(key, data) {\n            // Simple decryption algorithm\n            const decryptedData = crypto.subtle.decrypt({\n                name: 'AES-GCM',\n                iv: crypto.randomBytes(12),\n            }, key, Buffer.from(data, 'utf8'));\n            return decryptedData;\n        }\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
